definitions: a swimming stroke performed on the back with the arms lifted alternately out of the water in a backward circular motion and the legs extended and kicking

examples.text: I concentrated on the backstroke most of the time
I won the backstroke and breaststroke events
they would swim freestyle and then backstroke

shortDefinitions: swimming stroke performed on back with arms lifted alternately out of water in backward circular motion

definitions: a race, typically of a specified length or kind, in which the backstroke style of swimming is used

examples.text: he was fifth in the 200-meter backstroke

shortDefinitions: race in which such style of swimming is used
